OL,3,C'You can't just forget about it': WWII
OL,4,Cchild prisoners on life in Chinese
OL,5,Ccamps
OL,7,FAfter meeting for the first time it
OL,8,Fwas clear how excited they were to be
OL,9,Ftogether and how much comfort it
OL,10,Fbrought them to hear each other's
OL,11,Fexperiences - finally learning of
OL,12,Ftheir shared childhood but one they
OL,13,Fdidn't spend together.
OL,15,FIan's father was a missionary in China
OL,16,Fduring the war but the day after the
OL,17,Fattack on Pearl Harbour in 1941,
OL,18,FJapanese troops arrived at his home
OL,19,Fand took Ian and his family away.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
