OL,3,C'You can't just forget about it': WWII
OL,4,Cchild prisoners on life in Chinese
OL,5,Ccamps
OL,7,FThey were cramped into a small room,
OL,8,Fliving off rice and water, and were
OL,9,Fcompletely cut off from the outside
OL,10,Fworld.
OL,12,FAs young children they described how
OL,13,Fthey used to try and make their camp a
OL,14,Fhome.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
