OL,3,C'You can't just forget about it': WWII
OL,4,Cchild prisoners on life in Chinese
OL,5,Ccamps
OL,7,F"I remember my father lying in the
OL,8,Fdoorway of our little room, and I
OL,9,Fremember throwing water over him and
OL,10,Fthinking it was very funny and being
OL,11,Fvery upset when he was very angry
OL,12,Fbecause everyone in camp had to take a
OL,13,Ftwo-hour shift every day to pump water
OL,14,Fand that was our day's water supply,"
OL,15,FKatherine said.
OL,17,FIan said: "We actually reared a
OL,18,Fsparrow - we found a sparrow that had
OL,19,Fdropped out of his nest and we fed him
OL,20,Four rations or rice. And he lived!"
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
